text: <@U0548MM6B>: should I watch it?
is it worth my time?
Definintely
I watched the whole 12 hour season in a day
I'll give you what the Guardian had to say about it without spoilers
And other reviews I've read over the days
tbh it’s already on my plex
so I’m just waiting for an excuse to watch it haha
Good performance, takes a while to get started, but is definitely worth it in the end and it helps with the story because you're in the mind of the characters and don't know anything either.
Should make an even better season 2.
Some say it jumps from story to story (between the characters) and doesn't focus much on the main story. But I kind of like that, I find that interesting.
I dislike the concept of 1 big story in some series and I actually am interested in everyone's story if you know what I mean.
It takes the things we know today: open sexuality, gay rights and in general the modern society and it makes for an amazing series.

This is also so amazing about these new Netflix series, you can watch them anytime. (I don't know whether this is the case for TV series in America, but here in Belgium you'd probably have to wait till it's also available on DVD/Blu-ray)

When you start watching it, you'll be a bit like "WTF?". Just hang on and it'll get clear and fucking amazing.
noted
I personally think the combination of the Wachowski's and Straczynski is amazing.

The Wachowski's never back out of a daring project and one that can fail miserably, like this one (this can easily be overdone with action and everyone's powers can be abused in the series, which is not the case)

Straczynski's cinematography is also just amazing. The shots you get in the series are beautiful, it's amazingly done how the characters interact. It's fluid but even though a bit weird and the camera shows that perfectly.
Those are the producers and writers btw
I don't really follow the whole scene of Hollywood, these people are just amazing writers and producers.
(and the Wachowski's are the directors)
